quot;I \n&gt; am experiencing & I am acting&quot; an=\r\nd gets bound. When one realizes the \n&gt; true doers of various experiences & =\r\nactions, one is free.\n&gt; \n&gt; The gross, subtle and astral realms of existence=\r\n (bhur, bhuvar and \n&gt; suvar) are controlled by Fire, Wind and Sun. For any =\r\nmovement of prana \n&gt; in those realms, they are experiencers & doers and not=\r\n &quot;I&quot;. The &quot;I&quot; is \n&gt; untouched by those experiences and actions.\n&gt; \n&gt; Then w=\r\ne have the mind, which is the window through which we are aware of \n&gt; all t=\r\nhe realms of existence. It is controlled by Moon. Any experiences \n&gt; or act=\r\nions arising in mind are experienced or done by Moon and not by \n&gt; &quot;I&quot;.\n&gt; \n=\r\n&gt; Then we have destiny, which is the agent through which one&#39;s past karmas =\r\n\n&gt; (actions) are remembered and brought to fructification. It is controlled=\r\n \n&gt; by stars (nakshatras). Any experience or action arising through destiny=\r\n \n&gt; is experienced or done by nakshatras and not by &quot;I&quot;.\n&gt; \n&gt; Then we have =\r\nindriyas, which are the agents through which we connect to \n&gt; the world, i.=\r\ne. perceive it and modify it. They are controlled by \n&gt; Parjanya. Though Pa=\r\nrjanya is translated as a raincloud, it is from the \n&gt; root &quot;pR^ic&quot;, which =\r\nmeans &quot;to join&quot;. Parjanya shows connecting with \n&gt; others, which is what in=\r\ndriyas do. Parjanya is also used as a synonym \n&gt; for Indra, who owns indriy=\r\nas. So indriyas are controlled by Parjanya and \n&gt; any experiences or action=\r\ns arising though senses are experienced or done \n&gt; by Parjanya and not by &quot;=\r\nI&quot;.\n&gt; \n&gt; Then we have time, which is the agent through which we experience =\r\n\n&gt; memories and notions or now, earlier and later. It is controlled by \n&gt; S=\r\namvatsara or Time personified. Any experience or action arising through \n&gt; =\r\nmemories or expectations or other notions of time, is experienced or \n&gt; don=\r\ne by Samvatsara and not by &quot;I&quot;.\n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt; \n&gt; Bottomline: W=\r\nhen one experiences or acts using gross, subtle and astral \n&gt; bodies, mind,=\r\n destiny, indriyas and notion of time, one gets bound by \n&gt; thinking that &quot;=\r\nI am experiencing&quot; or &quot;I am doing&quot;. Instead, by realizing \n&gt; that &quot;I&quot; am no=\r\nt experiencing or doing, but Agni, Vayu, Surya, Chandrama, \n&gt; Nakshatras, P=\r\narjanya and Time, who arose when a vibration arose in Self, \n&gt; are experien=\r\ncing and acting through one&#39;s gross, subtle and astral \n&gt; bodies, mind, des=\r\ntiny, indriyas and notion of time, respectively, one \n&gt; becomes established=\r\n in Self. By knowing the true experiencer and actor \n&gt; of each experience a=\r\nnd action, one is freed from the false notion that \n&gt; &quot;I am experiencing&quot; a=\r\nnd &quot;I am acting&quot; and becomes free.\n&gt; \n&gt; This fuller understanding came in a=\r\nn inspired moment and I am unlikely \n&gt; to be able to refine it further for =\r\nnow.\n&gt; \n&gt; Best regards,\n&gt; Narasimha\n&gt; -------------------------------------=\r\n------------------------------\n&gt;    Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Les=\r\nsons, Jyotish Writings,\n&gt; &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam a=\r\nnd Pitri Tarpana:\n&gt;                    http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n&gt;    =\r\n   Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org\n&gt;       Spiritua=\r\nlity: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\n&gt;    Jyotish writings: htt=\r\np://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n&gt;                       Twitter =\r\nID: @homam108\n&gt; -----------------------------------------------------------=\r\n--------\n&gt; \n&gt; --- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@&gt;=\r\n wrote:\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; 