, it means riligious \n&gt; &gt; ceremonies also, but=\r\n note that a religious ceremony is supposed to be \n&gt; &gt; an inspired and bala=\r\nnced action.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; In my view, apas above means action and Apas means an =\r\nequanimous \n&gt; &gt; action, i.e. action where the doer is established in Self.\n=\r\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; *        *        *\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; The physical, mental and spiritual real=\r\nms are controlled by Fire, Wind \n&gt; &gt; and Sun gods. Fire, the transformer, c=\r\nreates the physical reality by \n&gt; &gt; processing the elements through the phy=\r\nsical senses and transforming \n&gt; &gt; them into physical experiences. Wind, th=\r\ne mover, creates the mental \n&gt; &gt; reality to by moving the notions and conce=\r\npts in the mind. Sun, the \n&gt; &gt; shiner, shows the spiritual reality by throw=\r\ning light on the divinity \n&gt; &gt; in everything. That is why we make aahutis t=\r\no fire, wind and Sun in \n&gt; &gt; uttarangam of a homam.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Whene Mantra pu=\r\nshpam refers to those three, it is saying that one who \n&gt; &gt; realizes that a=\r\nctions arise in the physical, mental & spiritual realms \n&gt; &gt; of one&#39;s being=\r\n, is established in Self. In other words, &quot;I&quot; am not \n&gt; &gt; doing actions, bu=\r\nt actions arise in parts of my being, which are \n&gt; &gt; repsented by fire, win=\r\nd and Sun. Next, it is saying that one who \n&gt; &gt; realizes that equanimous ac=\r\ntion arising in Self is the source of all \n&gt; &gt; these realms of being (physi=\r\ncal, mental and spiritual), is established \n&gt; &gt; in Self.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; In other w=\r\nords, equanimous actions arising in Self give rise to \n&gt; &gt; various aspects =\r\nof one&#39;s being. And actions arise in various aspects \n&gt; &gt; of one&#39;s being. O=\r\nne who realizes this and does not entertain notions \n&gt; &gt; that &quot;I am doing, =\r\nI did this ritual&quot; etc will be established in Self.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; This the main p=\r\nurport.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Best regards,\n&gt; &gt; Narasimha\n&gt;\n\n\n\n"}}